headline: A standoff between BlackRock and the FDIC is dragging into 2025
summary: A clash between BlackRock and the FDIC over the money manager’s holdings of US banks will play out in the waning days of President Joe Biden’s administration.

headline: BlackRock Receives Deadline From FDIC for Passivity Agreement
summary: BLK receives a deadline from the FDIC to accept the passivity agreement by Jan. 10, enabling the regulator to raise scrutiny over investments in FDIC-regulated banks.
